Below is a designer‑facing teardown of **MathCo.com** – covering its colour system, gradients, typography, layout components, and the way those elements are orchestrated on every key page.  Think of it as a spec you can hand directly to a UI‑ or brand‑designer.

---

## 1  Brand & Visual Language at a Glance

MathCo’s refreshed identity (“Own Your Intelligence”) is built around a **deep‑violet → indigo gradient, balanced by mint‑to‑teal accents and plenty of neutral space**.  Large, open headlines (set in the geometric‑sans **Inter** family) and roomy 16‑/20‑px body copy give the site a calm, enterprise‑grade feel.  Rounded‑corner cards, micro‑interactions on hover, and illustrated “spark” icons reinforce a friendly tone without sacrificing professionalism.  ([MathCo][1], [MathCo][2])

